How about calling it `scope`?

```ts
mutationFn(vars, context) {
   if (context.meta.something) {
     // ...
   }
   return fetch('...');
},
onMutate(_vars, context) {
  if (context.client) {
     // ...
  }
  const scope = {foo: 'bar'}
  return scope;
},
onSuccess(_data, _vars, scope) {
  console.log(scope)
}
```
